I mean, I think I am like a &quot;standard warrior&quot;, and I may be able to solo 1 mob, but then the healing time would be a pain (I don't have fungi nor money to buy it).<br>
<br>
Or maybe I do something wrong : using a ToD, 3460HP unbuff (I know, but this is the best I can get for now, with ND1), regen3, and a 44/44 for damage.<br>
<br>
Only spot I seem to solo efficiently is these archers in Echo Caverns, but unless I'm not at the right spot, there are only 2 archers there, on a 28min pop time...<br>
<br>
So, the only option would be grouping. <br>
I won't mind much if only I could go in a dungeon, find a group, and doing good XP when I have only 1 to 2hours to spare, time to time, for XP. Like it was pre-4th september. I could go to Sebilis and do some XP. Not astounishing, but almost decent, and I didn't care much, afterall for 1-2hours of XP-Grinding, it was fine. Now, you earn less. Better than before the XP-Fix , but less than before the XP-Nerf.<br>
<br>
I'm not complaining at all, I'm just seeing that warriors and rogues (and clerics before the patch) are not &quot;casual gamers&quot; classes, when speaking of XP Grinding.<br>
I re-rolled a monk for fun, and now when I have some time to spare for XP, I level him, much fun for now <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
Only thing that could solve this problem are either something to help warriors (and rogues, don't forget them <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  ) to solo, or Raiding-XP.<br>
Or both, afterall they gave clerics the ability to solo <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
