Last time I tested shrooms in Fungus, though I had 500HP less it was before the resists change, and with VoG on me I had to run to the zone.<br>
<br>
I never tested spiders in VL, though, so I may give it a try (I don't have my ToD since long).<br>
What restrained me on VL is the constant crowd in there, 'tis hard to find a mob <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <br>
<br>
I know I can solo Jin casters in Sebilis either, but there are too many light blues casters, and I didn't tested non-casters type like Sebilis Golem or Dar Knight (tested duo'ing with a monk friend, had to let the monk tank, better with mend).<br>
<br>
Maybe I should give a try to The Grey, with 2H-Kitting, it may worth it, as far as I know mobs there don't hit for much (not talking about the rock things).<br>
<br>
Like I said, solo'ing 1 mob isn't impossible, I'm sure I can solo some mobs if I use the right tactic. But the recovery time with bind wounds and/or BP is too much to worth it.<br>
But once again I'm not even complaining, just saying that with the expected XP-Raid it would be far better for warriors and rogues casual gamers, and that with the change about clerics that can solo, we could eventually expect the same thing for rogues and warriors (not that we can't solo, but it isn't worth it if you haven't got the right gear and if you do not hunt at the right place, and if you don't have a lot of HPs that means, from my point of vue, a decent gear to start with).<br>
The main argument to give clerics the ability to solo was, according to Verant, the need to be less group-dependant, to have a lil' more freedom in their choices of XP-Grinding, especially now that they plan to give spells to Shaman/Druids to not make Clerics a mandatory class in any XP group.<br>
I think this argument applies to warriors (not saying we aren't useful, just saying we aren't necessary), and to rogues.<br>
<br>
